
EXCEPTION TEST ISOLATION


MOTIVATION:
Test cases are created to find bugs and
situations where exceptions may arise. However, in some
cases, it can be necessary to induce a particular exception
condition to test whether the system handles it correctly. In
such cases, it is possible to isolate the exception handling in
a specific test case.

MECHANICS:
- Create a test method for testing the exception
- Extract the exception testing from the existing test case
- Create

